  "text": "A look at the currents of Indian history, Punjab's role seen as momentous as Punjab has an eccentric history of industrial development [CITATION_1] . Post green revolution has been quintessential with sobriquets like prosperity and progression, particularly compared to the rest of India. Till pre liberalization era, the industrial development in Punjab located to only urban areas connected with G.T. road, namely, Jalandhar, Phagwara, Ludhiana, Khanna, and Mandi Gobindgarh [CITATION_2] . Statically, the total number of registered units in Punjab was 74%. 69% of the industrial workers employed in the state. Therefore, the Punjab state witnessed sheersided development till pre liberalization era.",
